parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft position sensor can cause the check engine light to illuminate, the engine to stall, and potentially lead to engine damage, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light is illuminated
the vehicle hesitates or loses power
smoke or fumes come from the hose
and a metal burning smell is present.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Issues with Camshaft Position Sensor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The recall issues with the camshaft position sensor can cause frustration and financial burden for vehicle owners, as they may be unable to find a dealer to honor the recall or may be charged for repairs.
symptoms: Dealers refuse to honor the recall
and consumers are unable to locate authorized service centers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to complete air bag recall repairs can lead to a higher risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident, as the air bag system may not function properly.
symptoms: failure of air bags to deploy in an accident
inability to locate a dealer to honor the recall

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dealer Unavailability and Refusal to Honor Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of dealerships or their refusal to honor the recall can lead to a delay or inability to complete necessary repairs, potentially putting drivers at risk.
symptoms: inability to locate a dealer to honor the recall
dealer refusing to work on the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Bag Failure and Deployment Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of air bags to deploy or deploy properly can lead to a higher risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Hose Failure and Unavailability of Dealership Service
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hose can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle. The unavailability of dealership service can delay or prevent necessary repairs, further increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: as the complaints primarily focus on the inability to obtain service from dealerships.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure and Warping of Rotors
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause accidents or loss of control of the vehicle. Warping of rotors can lead to further brake problems and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: disc brake freezing in the closed position
and metal-to-metal contact on the disc brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause accidents, which can result in injury or death.

Intermittent brake failure can cause accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Steering and brake system failure can cause accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
